SIMPLE: oculomotor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oculomotor
<hw>Oc`u*lo*mo"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Oculo-</ets> + <ets>motor</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to the movement of the eye; -- applied especially
to the common motor nerves (or third pair of cranial nerves) which
supply many of the muscles of the orbit.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>The oculomotor nerve.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oculonasal</ent>⟦br⟧
